- Physical ghost mass: m₂ ~ 0.5–2 Planck masses
- Ghost mass divergence mechanism (Becker-Ripken) is ruled out since g₃* ≠ 0
- Black hole instability threshold at r_H ≈ 0.63 Planck lengths — sub-Planckian, hidden in the non-perturbative regime

**More info:** `current_hunts/atlas/execution/instances/quantum-gravity-2/strategies/strategy-004/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`

